> **Dependencia:** `framer-motion` so deve ser usado quando estiver em `package.json` / aprovado em `docs/06_SPECIFICATION.md`. Se o pacote nao estiver instalado, nao importar Motion; use CSS transitions ou adicione a dep com justificativa.

# Padroes Framer Motion

## Core Props
- `initial`: estado antes da animacao (offscreen state)
- `animate`: estado final (onscreen state)
- `exit`: estado de saida (requer AnimatePresence pai)
- `transition`: configuracao de timing/physics
- `variants`: mapa nomeado de estados para orquestrar filhos

## Spring Physics (padrao para tudo)
Preferir springs sobre duracoes fixas — resultado mais natural.

```tsx
const springDefault = { type: "spring", stiffness: 200, damping: 20 };
const springSnappy = { type: "spring", stiffness: 300, damping: 25 };
const springGentle = { type: "spring", stiffness: 100, damping: 15 };
const springBouncy = { type: "spring", stiffness: 250, damping: 12 };
```

- stiffness 100-300: quanto menor, mais lenta e suave
- damping 12-30: quanto menor, mais bounce
- mass: manter em 1 (padrao) na maioria dos casos

## Timing Guidelines
- Micro-interacoes (hover, tap, toggle): 120-220ms
- Entrance (fade in, slide in): 300-600ms
- Exit (fade out, slide out): 200-400ms
- Stagger entre filhos: 50-100ms
- MAXIMO absoluto: 400ms para qualquer animacao de UI (exceto scroll-linked)

## GPU-Only — Regra Inquebravel
Animar SOMENTE `transform` e `opacity`. Nunca:
- ❌ width, height, top, left, margin, padding
- ❌ border-radius, box-shadow (compositing caro)
- ❌ background-color (exceto em opacity crossfade)
- ✅ x, y, scale, rotate, opacity
- ✅ clipPath (para reveals)

## Scroll Animations — whileInView
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 40 }}
  whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px", amount: 0.2 }}
  transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 200, damping: 20 }}
>
  {children}
</motion.div>
```
- `once: true` SEMPRE (animar apenas na primeira vez)
- `margin: "-100px"` para disparar antes de entrar no viewport
- `amount: 0.2` para disparar quando 20% visivel

## Scroll-Linked (Parallax / Progress)
```tsx
const { scrollYProgress } = useScroll({ target: ref, offset: ["start end", "end start"] });
const y = useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0, 1], [100, -100]);
const opacity = useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0, 0.3, 0.7, 1], [0, 1, 1, 0]);
```
- useScroll para obter progresso normalizado 0-1
- useTransform para mapear progresso em valores de animacao
- Ideal para parallax, progress bars, reveal sections

## Page Transitions
```tsx
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  <motion.main
    key={pathname}
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
    animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -20 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
  >
    {children}
  </motion.main>
</AnimatePresence>
```
- `mode="wait"`: exit completa antes de enter comecar
- key DEVE mudar entre paginas (usar pathname)
- Exit deve ser mais rapido que enter

## Variants — Orquestrar Filhos
```tsx
const containerVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.08, delayChildren: 0.1 }
  }
};

const itemVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 30 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { type: "spring", stiffness: 200, damping: 20 } }
};

<motion.ul variants={containerVariants} initial="hidden" whileInView="visible" viewport={{ once: true }}>
  {items.map((item) => (
    <motion.li key={item.id} variants={itemVariants}>{item.name}</motion.li>
  ))}
</motion.ul>
```

