## Acessibilidade — prefers-reduced-motion
```tsx
import { useReducedMotion } from "framer-motion";

function AnimatedComponent({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const shouldReduce = useReducedMotion();

  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={shouldReduce ? false : { opacity: 0, y: 40 }}
      whileInView={shouldReduce ? {} : { opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      viewport={{ once: true }}
    >
      {children}
    </motion.div>
  );
}
```
- SEMPRE verificar prefers-reduced-motion
- Quando ativado: sem movimento, apenas fade suave ou nenhuma animacao
- Hook useReducedMotion retorna boolean

## Performance
- Nunca animar propriedades de layout (width, height, top, left)
- Usar will-change: transform apenas se necessario (browser hint)
- Testar animacoes com CPU 4x throttle no DevTools
- layout prop APENAS quando realmente precisa de layout animation (caro)
- Evitar AnimatePresence em listas longas (>20 itens)
- Profile com React DevTools antes de fazer ship
